news.title: Maharashtra CM to inaugurate two new Mumbai Metro lines on April 2
news.para: Metro services on the first phase of Line 2A and also Line 7, both in western suburbs, will be thrown open for commuter use, Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority (MMRDA) commissioner SVR Srinivas said.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government sets January 2023 deadline for comprehensive land survey
news.para: The officials told chief minister YS Jagan Mohan Reddy at a review meeting at his Tadepalli camp office on Thursday that they were working to complete land survey and issue clear titles in 5,200 villages by the end of July 2023, 5,700 villages by the end of August 2023 and 6,460 villages by the end of September 2023.

news.title: Lying idle for 10 years, YEIDA takes back plots from firms
news.para: In total, the industrial authority took back around 2.2 lakh sqmt from the private developers and passed an order to forfeit Rs 27.3 crore that they had deposited.

news.title: Property registrations in Vizianagaram see marginal drop in FY22
news.para: The stamps and registration department which collects a percentage for registration of properties such as flats, houses, lands, and others is one of the top revenue contributors.

news.title: Haryana CM to hold round table meet on Global City project
news.para: According to officials, the land on which the Global City project is set to come up is a part of an area that had been transferred to Reliance Industries in 2006 to be developed as a special economic zone (SEZ).

news.title: Ludhiana civic body earns Rs 2 crore as 5,000 clear property tax dues on last day
news.para: However, officials in MC zone B also sealed six properties from where property tax had been pending for long. The owners paid Rs 29.5 lakh on the spot after which the seal was opened.

news.title: Hindva is set to deliver the first-of-its-kind Strata Sales & Leaseback model with the delivery of 'The World'
news.para: A combination of Hotel, Serviced Residences, Recreational & Commercial zone, etc.

news.title: Pune civic body to reconsider renting out its properties at Rs 1 per month
news.para: The move by the elected members was seen as an effort to gain political mileage for when the civic elections are held. However, the civic administration feels that a paltry Re1 monthly rent is not economically viable.

news.title: Rebate period for property taxpayers starts today in Chandigarh
news.para: Owners of residential properties will get 20% rebate on the total tax amount, while owners of commercial properties will be able to avail 10% rebate if they pay during the two-month rebate period.

news.title: Building permit revenue drops by 53% within a year in Thiruvananthapuram
news.para: Lack of optimism is evident in the estimate expected for 2022-23, as well as the estimated amount from collection of building permit fee is set at Rs 20 crore; even lesser than what was expected during the previous fiscal.

news.title: Rajasthan: Now, deposit urban development tax by June 30
news.para: The government has fixed the provision of 50% rebate on principal arrears and 100% rebate on penalty on deposit of house tax on residential/commercial plots/buildings from April 1, 2022 to June 30, 2022.

news.title: Max Ventures case: NCLT adjourns hearing over Neelu Analjit Singh's petition
news.para: Senior advocate Guru Krishna Kumar, appearing for Neelu Analjit Singh informed the bench that they have received a reply from Max Ventures Investment Holdings and sought a week's time to file a rejoinder over it.

news.title: Over Rs 1,131-crore stamp duty collected in March in Mumbai
news.para: The performance has surpassed the previous high of Rs 875 crore touched in March 2021, when homebuyers had taken advantage of lower stamp duty benefit.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC's property tax collection up by 10% in a year
news.para: Last time, owing to the pandemic, the BMC was able to collect Rs 5,090 crore as property tax till the end of the financial year which this time it hoped to surpass with the Covid situation in the city coming under control.

news.title: Telangana HC notice to Ramky group over Dharani fraud plea
news.para: Justice B Vijaysen Reddy ordered notices while hearing a petition filed by Yatam Murali of Saroornagar, who charged the revenue officials of fraud to extend the undue benefit to Ramky.
